column5: Friday I went to a kawartha lake to fish walleye with a friend that has been catching muskie every time we fish we want walleye, we use little walleye baits and line and rods and reels but still they keep hitting our baits  I caught some real small muskie maybe 22 or 24 inches, it's good to see the small ones, some day they will be big  and we did alright with the walleye but my friend seems to get lots and big muskie everytime we fish the kawarthas  here are some pictures and if you have nothing to do for 3 minutes you can watch the video of the last couple of minutes bringing in the fish  the line was wrapped around the tail but it was hooked in the mouth just as I tried to net it the line pulled on the tail the fish jumped the hooks caught in the net and twisted the mess, so it wasn't about to go in the net  the next time the fish tried to get free it came loose form the hooks but pushed more into the net I grabbed the fish and got it in the boat  the camera was hanging from my neck so it's not very good....but it's there if you want to see it             <object width="425" height="350"> <param name="movie" value="
Excellent report Terry....a super video clip as well!
That's one nice sized accidental musky.
what a great accidental catch!!!!!  cheers!
Can I go "walleye" fishing with you guys? That is a beauty! -Brian

We got to get out together.  every time I go out musky fishing I'm catching those dang pesky 'eyes!  i've landed more walleye than musky so far this year.  Smallest lure i've caught them on is super shadrap
Nice Musky!
Awesome!!
As I always say, good things happen when you least expect it. Well done
Awesome report Terry.  Nice Pickerel and Musky.  Way to go.    Joey  p.s.  Nice net job
Nice Musky and walleye thanks for sharing the video and pics.
nice.
Thats funny,I go bass fish,n and catch pike.LOL  Very cool vid bud and a real nice musky.
Nice thick fish, very impressive.

My son and I were out on Scugog on Saturday and managed 4 Walleye and 4 incidental Musky and I think one of the Musky we caught twice none were as nice as your incidental.  BTW we saw no floating Carp or aliens and there were lots of birds.
nice fish!
Cool report Terry!  The video is a very nice touch.  Sorry to hear about your "accidental" musky...LOL.  You guys boated a few nice fish...so that's success in my books!
Good stuff Terry, that's a beautiful musky your bud caught.  Maybe I'll start carrying some little pickeral lures in the boat for when the normal musky baits aren't doing anything productive
Wow! Great fish and the video was a real treat. Thanks Terry.  Cheers, 1leg
Great report Terry!!!    video too!
